    "narrative": "For this slate, **Corbin Carroll** (75.04) stands out as our clear anchor, benefiting from a favorable middle-of-the-order slot and a strong xwOBA profile against Sproat. While the park factors for **Corbin Carroll** are slightly suppressed, his dynamic platoon edge and overall pedigree make him the safest ceiling play in our lineup. Following closely is **Josh Naylor** (72.22), whose score is significantly bolstered by a plus-matchup against Bradley and a move into the cleanup spot, granting him excellent RBI potential. We are also looking for a productive day from **Kyle Karros** (63.78) and **James Wood** (62.73), both of whom are projected to outperform their baselines due to high-leverage lineup positions and favorable wind conditions that should aid their power profiles.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was **Austin Riley** (43.75), who narrowly missed the starting lineup cut. While **Austin Riley** has the raw talent to change a game, the optimizer heavily penalized him for a brutal matchup against Skubal, whose elite SP_xERA (2.71) triggered a 19% downward adjustment to his base score. We also opted to sit **Jose Caballero** (39.32), whose poor BvP metrics against Eovaldi and a bottom-tier lineup spot pushed him below our 40-point efficiency floor. We are keeping a close eye on **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (52.10) and **Alex Freeland** (51.51); both face difficult pitchers in Eovaldi and Alcantara respectively, meaning their production will be highly sensitive to their ability to mitigate high-end starting pitching. \n\nFinally, please note that while the weather looks mostly favorable, the 6.11 SP_xERA for Williamson makes **Mickey Moniak** (56.32) and **Kyle Karros** (63.78) high-upside plays despite their less-than-ideal lineup slots. Managers should monitor **Luis Campusano** (46.24) closely; as our #9 hitter against Taillon, his path to value is narrow, and any pinch-hit scenario later in the game could jeopardize his limited plate appearances. Remain patient with **Trevor Story** (59.77), whose BvP edge (27 PA) provides a rare stability boost that keeps him firmly in the \"Strong\" start category today.",
